ze and optimize Windows 11. Since broad \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/windows-10-losing-support-microsoft-365/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esupport of Windows 10 ends in October 2025\u003c/a\u003e, it will work only with the long-term servicing channel versions (LTSC).\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThis is designed for Windows 11. However, due to a lack of functionality, the developer turned it into a proper C# app. Whatever the case, you can now download the Winhance app on your PC. However, it is essential to mention that it only works on 64-bit versions of Windows.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWith Winhance\u0026#39;s background noted, it’s a good time to explore its capabilities, features, and functionality. Winhance is a free and fully open-source app. A new legend at the top of the screen lets you know if apps can be reinstalled once removed. Windhance will save a script and a scheduled task if something is removed. So even if something gets installed via Windows Update that you previously selected to remove, it will remove it again during startup.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eOne of the most significant benefits in my book is the ability to uninstall needless Windows apps. For instance, I used the tool to uninstall Bing search, Copilot, 3D Viewer, Maps, and other Windows features I do not use. It also removes things like the \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/reasons-hyper-v-best-hypervisor-windows/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eHyper-V hypervisor\u003c/a\u003e and provides many alternative browsers, such as Brave, DuckDuckGo, Arc, and Vivaldi. Again, it allows you to add what you want and remove the rest.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"74b8-490d-ab2cc633ec55\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/ways-optimize-windows-11-productivity-creativity/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"5682\" height=\"3197\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A Windows 11 laptop showing Flow launcher settings and the search bar\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/flow-launcher-on-windows-11.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"using-winhance\"\u003e\n                        Using Winhance\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"tweak-windows-11-to-take-back-control-of-windows-from-microsoft\"\u003e\n            Tweak Windows 11 to take back control of Windows from Microsoft\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Software \u0026amp; Apps section will be front and center, starting with the main screen. This allows you to uninstall Windows apps and capabilities you want to remove. For instance, I can remove Microsoft apps like Edge and Copilot, which I love to remove. Check the legend at the top of the screen to see if you can read it from the Winhance utility. Then check or uncheck the features you want to include with your Windows install. It is as simple as that.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eI wish it included more customization tools; it’s a bit light on those. However, it provides customization features like StartAllBack, OpenShell, and Nilesoft Shell. Other free, open-source customization options are missing, like Windhawk, Lively Wallpaper, and Rainmeter, which are great tools. The options in Windhawk are endless, so you will still need to download them separately.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIt also includes storage and security apps like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/reasons-chose-proton-vpn-over-others/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eProton VPN\u003c/a\u003e and Proton Drive. That entices me since I am part of the Proton Unlimited ecosystem. It allows you to try free (but limited) Proton apps if you don’t have a subscription. Winhance has compression utilities like 7-Zip and WinRAR. There are multimedia apps like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/hidden-features-in-vlc/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eVLC\u003c/a\u003e, Audacity, foobar2000, and Spotify. I only need VLC since it can play virtually any media file you throw at it. Choosing apps and utilities reminds me of a limited tool like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/reasons-use-ninite-instead-unigetui-install-open-source-apps/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eNinite\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/reasons-unigetui-best-package-manager-windows/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eUniGetUI\u003c/a\u003e. But I digress.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                                \n        \n                            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"939f-4148-951a945b26cc\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                            \n                        \t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;Image credit: Windhawk\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=480\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=480\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=320\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=320\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=300\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=300\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Windhawk logo\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windhawk-logo-1.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\n\n        \n        \n                            \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\tWindhawk\n\t\t\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                                    \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n                    \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"customize-and-optimize-windows-settings\"\u003e\n                        Customize and optimize Windows settings\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"fine-tune-the-windows-11-experience-for-your-workflow\"\u003e\n            Fine-tune the Windows 11 experience for your workflow\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Shows software and apps successfully removed from Winhance\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/11-successfully-removed-winhance.png\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Putting aside the glaring absence of Windhawk and other apps, removing unneeded Windows apps from your Windows install is the main feature. Once I selected what I wanted for apps and selected to get rid of the Microsoft bloat I didn’t want, I ran the Winhance tool to install apps by clicking \u003cstrong\u003eInstall Selected Items\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAfter your apps are installed, removing Windows features is a separate action. Make sure to check the legend at the top to verify if a Windows feature can be reinstalled. When you are ready, click the \u003cstrong\u003eRemove Selected Items\u003c/strong\u003e button. Wait a few minutes, and your chosen Windows items will be successfully removed from your installation. I selected Copilot, which removed the core version on Windows, but it was still in the apps it\u0026#39;d crept into, like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/reasons-encrypt-email-outlook-app-windows-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethe Outlook app\u003c/a\u003e and Notepad. So, you will still need to turn off Copilot in those apps.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"fe6a-49e5-8bbabeba0e8f\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/completely-remove-copilot-on-windows-11-apps-its-crept-into/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"6000\" height=\"3376\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Close-up of the Microsoft 365 Copilot listing on the Microsoft Store\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/microsoft-365-copilot.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/completely-remove-copilot-on-windows-11-apps-its-crept-into/\" title=\"5 reasons I completely remove Copilot on Windows 11 from all apps it’s crept into\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\t5 reasons I completely remove Copilot on Windows 11 from all apps it’s crept into\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eMicrosoft want to force Copilot AI into your apps on Windows, but I remove it for a better experience.l\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"winhance-is-an-open-source-utility-for-customizing-the-windows-experience-on-your-pc\"\u003e\n            Winhance is an open-source utility for customizing the Windows experience on your PC\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWinhance is a valuable open-source utility to keep in your toolbox when you install Windows 11. It helps remove the Windows bloat you don’t want and installs other helpful apps for different tasks. Keep in mind that the amount of time it takes to remove Windows features will depend on the number of items you choose. But in my experience, removing a handful of features was successful, and the app is responsive.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
